HEADWORD: Listerism
<hw>Lis"ter*ism</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧s"t⟦etil⟧r*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The systematic use of antiseptics in the
performance of operations and the treatment of wounds; -- so called from
<person>Joseph <etsep>Lister</etsep></person>, an English
surgeon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

